"Pensacola is the westernmost city in the Florida Panhandle and the county seat of Escambia County, Florida, United States. As of the 2010 census, the city had a total population of 51,923. Pensacola is the principal city of the Pensacola-Ferry Pass-Brent Metropolitan Statistical Area, an area with about 455,102 residents in 2009. Pensacola was founded in 1559 by a Spanish explorer named Tristan de Luna y Arellano. It was officially America's first settlement."@en
